version_description: This version is much easier to play then the other versions that I saw on here
Should be correct chords and correct placement, but feel free to correct. Enjoy.
Easy, and for extra flair, you can replace Em with G. The violin intro follows the Am chord, and is easy to figure out.
I use different chords that are more accurate to how the song is actually played.

It feels more comfortable to use.  Additionally, most of my tabs already posted have power chords used instead of major or minor. This is to take away having to switch to minor or major format.  Easier, in my views.  If I'm wrong, I will gladly change it.  But none of the "some of the chords are minor, and this is very important in a chords tab" responses.  It's a tab, after all, not an official statement for what the band itself uses.
